  <skos:Concept rdf:about="https://linked.data.gov.au/def/anzsrc-seo/2020/2111">
    <skos:prefLabel xml:lang="en">Pacific Peoples health</skos:prefLabel>
    <skos:notation>2111</skos:notation>
    <skos:inScheme rdf:resource="https://linked.data.gov.au/def/anzsrc-seo/2020"/>
    <skos:broader rdf:resource="https://linked.data.gov.au/def/anzsrc-seo/2020/21"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">This group covers R&amp;D directed towards the public health of Pacific Peoples. It includes the study of social and cultural factors affecting the health of Pacific Peoples and the delivery of health services to these communities.</skos:definition>
    <skos:scopeNote xml:lang="en">a) The diagnosis, prevention and treatment of clinical conditions for non-Indigenous communities is included in Group 2001 Clinical health.
b) Evaluation of health and support services and health policies for non-Indigenous communities is included in Group 2002 Evaluation of health and support services.
c) Provision of health and support services for non-Indigenous communities is included in Group 2003 Provision of health and support services.
d) Health as it pertains to the general population and non-Indigenous communities is included in Group 2004 Public health (excl. specific population health) and Group 2005 Specific population health (excl. Indigenous health).</skos:scopeNote>
